<paragraph blockId="23.[683,1215,406,1528]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">
IDENTIFICATION: We consulted descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[909,1114,646,670]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">
<emphasis box="[909,1114,646,670]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Artibeus planirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." box="[719,872,680,704]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 282" refId="ref37541" refString="Husson, A. M. 1962. The bats of Suriname. Zoologische Verhandelingen (Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie, Leiden) 58: 1 - 282." type="journal article" year="1962">Husson (1962</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Husson, A. M." box="[885,939,681,705]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" refId="ref37570" refString="Husson, A. M. 1978. The mammals of Suriname. Zoologische Monographieen van het Rijksmuseum van Natuurlijke Historie (Leiden) 2: 569 pp. + 151 pls." type="book" year="1978">1978</bibRefCitation>
), 
<bibRefCitation author="Patten, D. R." box="[961,1108,681,705]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" refId="ref40939" refString="Patten, D. R. 1971. A review of the large species of Artibeus (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) from western South America, Ph. D. dissertation, Texas A &amp; M University, College Station, 194 pp." type="book" year="1971">Patten (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Handley, C. O., Jr." pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="163 - 172" refId="ref36981" refString="Handley, C. O., Jr. 1987. New species of mammals from northern South America: fruit-eating bats, genus Artibeus Leach. Fieldiana Zoology, New Series 39: 163 - 172." type="book chapter" year="1987">Handley (1987)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brosset, A. &amp; P. Charles-Dominique" box="[761,1161,715,739]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="509 - 560" refId="ref33466" refString="Brosset, A., and P. Charles-Dominique. 1990. The bats from French Guiana: a taxonomic, faunistic and ecological approach. Mammalia 54: 509 - 560." type="journal article" year="1990">Brosset and Charles-Dominique (1990)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lim, B. K. &amp; D. E. Wilson" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="763 - 768" refId="ref38453" refString="Lim, B. K., and D. E. Wilson. 1993. Taxonomic status of Artibeus amplus (Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae) in northern South America. Journal of Mammalogy 74: 763 - 768." type="journal article" year="1993">Lim and Wilson (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lim, B. K." box="[893,1011,749,773]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="65 - 71" refId="ref38414" refString="Lim, B. K. 1997. Morphometric differentiation and species status of the allopatric fruit-eating bats Artibeus jamaicensis and A. planirostris in Venezuela. Studies on Neotropical Fauna and Environment 32: 65 - 71." type="journal article" year="1997">Lim (1997)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hollis, L." box="[1023,1160,749,773]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref37294" refString="Hollis, L. 2005. Artibeus planirostris. Mammalian Species 775: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2005">Hollis (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lim, B. K." box="[686,854,783,807]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="225 - 274" refId="ref38551" refString="Lim, B. K., et al. 2005. Results of the ALCOA Foundation-Suriname expeditions. XIV. Mammals of Brownsberg Nature Park, Suriname. Annals of Carnegie Museum 74: 225 - 274." type="journal article" year="2005">Lim et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
. Currently three subspecies are recognized: 
<emphasis box="[778,893,818,842]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. fallax</emphasis>
(
<collectingCountry box="[907,1016,818,842]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
[south and east of the Orinoco river]), 
<collectingCountry box="[911,1006,852,876]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1020,1113,852,876]" name="Grenada" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Grenada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1127,1211,852,876]" name="Guyana" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[684,776,886,910]" name="Suriname" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Surinam</collectingCountry>
, French Guiana, and the lower Amazon basin of 
<collectingCountry box="[770,833,921,945]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), 
<emphasis box="[848,982,921,945]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. hercules</emphasis>
(southeastern 
<collectingCountry name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Colombia</collectingCountry>
and the eastern lowlands of 
<collectingCountry box="[1013,1101,955,979]" name="Ecuador" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1163,955,978]" name="Peru" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[685,762,989,1013]" name="Bolivia" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
), and 
<emphasis box="[831,1010,989,1013]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">
A. p. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" box="[894,1010,989,1013]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">planirostris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
(southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1134,1209,989,1013]" name="Bolivia" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[791,900,1023,1047]" name="Argentina" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[916,1016,1024,1048]" name="Paraguay" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, and eastern and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[783,845,1058,1082]" name="Brazil" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Marques-Aguiar, S. A." box="[865,1104,1058,1082]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="301 - 321" refId="ref39372" refString="Marques-Aguiar, S. A. 2008 (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Genus Artibeus Leach, 1821. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 301 - 321. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Marques-Aguiar, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). The only major morphological difference recognized among subspecies is that 
<emphasis box="[875,1016,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. hercules</emphasis>
tends to be larger than the other subspecies (
<bibRefCitation author="Hollis, L." box="[966,1097,1161,1185]" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 6" refId="ref37294" refString="Hollis, L. 2005. Artibeus planirostris. Mammalian Species 775: 1 - 6." type="journal article" year="2005">Hollis, 2005</bibRefCitation>
). Based on distribution, the voucher material from Mayo River basin should correspond to the subspecies 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">A. p. hercules</emphasis>
. However, measurements of our material span the published variation of size for the entire species, and hence do not conform to published characteristics of the subspecies. We therefore recommend against formally recognizing subspecies in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Spix" baseAuthorityYear="1823" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Artibeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="planirostris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="23">Artibeus planirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
until truly diagnostic characters can be found, including additional data from molecular markers.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
